) |title=Introduction to Tibetan Buddhism |date=2007 |publisher=[[Shambhala Publications]] |isbn=978-1-55939-835-0 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=cy980CH84mEC}}\n* {{Citation |editor1-last=Powers |editor1-first=John |author-link=John Powers (academic) |last=Powers |first=John |title=The Buddhist World |chapter=Buddhas and Buddhisms |date=2016 |publisher=[[Routledge]] |isbn=978-0-415-61044-5}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Prebish |first1=Charles S. |editor1-last=Williams |editor1-first=Paul |title=Buddhism: Critical Concepts in Religious Studies, 1: Early History in South and Southeast Asia |date=2005 |orig-year=1974 |publisher=[[Routledge]] |chapter=Review of Scholarship on Buddhist Councils |isbn=0-415-33227-3 |pages=224\u2013243}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Ray |first1=R.A. |author-link=Reginald Ray |title=Buddhist Saints in India: A Study in Buddhist Values and Orientations |date=1994 |publisher=[[Oxford University Press]] |isbn=0-19-507202-2}}\n* {{Citation|last1=Rhys Davids|first1=C.A.F. |author-link=C.A.F. Rhys Davids |title=Love (Buddhist) |editor1-last=Hastings|editor1-first=James|editor1-link=James Hastings|editor2-last=Selbie|editor2-first=John Alexander|editor3-last=Gray|editor3-first=Louis H.|editor3-link=Louis Herbert Gray |encyclopedia=Encyclopaedia of Religion and Ethics |oclc=614111002 |volume=8 |date=1914 |publisher=[[T. & T. Clark]]|url=https://archive.org/download/encyclopaediaofr08hastuoft/encyclopaediaofr08hastuoft.pdf |pages=159{{en dash}}162}}\n* {{Citation |last=Riggs |first=D.E. |year=2004 |title=Fukudenkai: Sewing the Buddha's Robe in Contemporary Japanese Buddhist Practice |journal=[[Japanese Journal of Religious Studies]] |pages=311\u2013356 |url=http://enlight.lib.ntu.edu.tw/FULLTEXT/JR-MAG/mag133932.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202175231/http://enlight.lib.ntu.edu.tw/FULLTEXT/JR-MAG/mag133932.pdf |archive-date=2 February 2020 |url-status=live}}\n* {{Citation |last=Riggs |first=D.E. |year=2007 |title=The Buddhist Robe According to the Teaching: Nyoh\u014de, N\u014de and Funz\u014de |journal=\u4f5b\u6559\u6587\u5316\u7814\u7a76\u6240\u7d00\u8981 [Institute of Buddhist Culture, [[Ryukoku University]]]|volume=46 |pages=A87\u2013A97 |url=https://opac.ryukoku.ac.jp/webopac/TD00343008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217194213/https://opac.ryukoku.ac.jp/webopac/KJ00005242162._?key=XAPZVQ |archive-date=17 February 2020 |url-status=live}}\n* {{Citation |doi=10.14277/2385-3042/AnnOr-53-17-12 |url=https://iris.unive.it/retrieve/handle/10278/3701137/132836/Multiple%20Layers%20of%20Transmission_Sanvido_AnnOr_53.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116141406/https://iris.unive.it/retrieve/handle/10278/3701137/132836/Multiple%2520Layers%2520of%2520Transmission_Sanvido_AnnOr_53.pdf |archive-date=16 November 2019 |url-status=live |journal=Annali di Ca' Foscari. Serie Orientale |issn=2385-3042 |volume=53 |year=2017 |title=Multiple Layers of Transmission: Gasan J\u014dseki and the Goi Doctrine in the Medieval S\u014dt\u014d school |first=Marta |last=Sanvido}}\n* {{Citation |last=Silk |first=J.A. |author-link=Jonathan Silk |date=2003 |title=Dressed for Success: The Monk K\u0101\u015byapa and Strategies of Legitimation in Earlier Mah\u0101y\u0101na Buddhist Scriptures |journal=[[Journal asiatique]] |volume=291 |issue=1\u20132 |pages=173\u2013219 |url=https://openaccess.leidenuniv.nl/bitstream/handle/1887/17730/Silk_Dressed%20For%20Success.pdf?sequence=1 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217191410/https://openaccess.leidenuniv.nl/bitstream/handle/1887/17730/Silk_Dressed%2520For%2520Success.pdf?sequence=1 |archive-date=17 February 2020 |url-status=live}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Strong |first1=J.S. |author-link=John S. Strong |title=The Legend and Cult of Upagupta: Sanskrit Buddhism in North India and Southeast Asia |date=1994 |publisher=[[Motilal Banarsidass Publishers]] |isbn=9788120811546 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=bKq7k2DegjcC}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Strong |first1=J.S. |authorlink1=John S. Strong |title=The Buddha: A Beginner's Guide |date=2001 |publisher=[[Oneworld Publications]] |isbn=978-1-78074-054-6}}\n* {{Citation |title=Relics of the Buddha|first=J.S. |last=Strong|author-link=John S. Strong |year=2007 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=_KLAxmR8PZAC |publisher=[[Princeton University Press]]|isbn=978-0-691-11764-5 }}\n* {{Citation |last1=Swearer|first1=D.K.|title=The Buddhist World of Southeast Asia|date=2010|publisher=[[State University of New York Press]]|isbn=978-1-4384-3251-9|edition=2nd}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Sujato |first1=Bhikkhu |last2=Brahmali |first2=Bhikkhu |title=Authenticity of the Early Buddhist Texts |date=2015 |journal= Journal of the Oxford Centre for Buddhist Studies |volume=5 |url=https://ocbs.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/authenticity.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224032237/http://ocbs.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/authenticity.pdf |archive-date=24 December 2015 |url-status=live}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Tambiah |first1=S.J. |authorlink1=Stanley Jeyaraja Tambiah |title=The Buddhist Saints of the Forest and the Cult of Amulets: A Study in Charisma, Hagiography, Sectarianism, and Millennial Buddhism |date=1984 |publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]] |isbn=978-0-521-27787-7}}\n* {{Citation |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20070614122021/http://dl-gamma.tccd.edu/academic/booklets/sp07/PHIL_1304.pdf |url=http://dl-gamma.tccd.edu/academic/booklets/sp07/PHIL_1304.pdf |archive-date=14 June 2007 |url-status=dead |title=Great Religions of the World |author=[[Tarrant County College]], Center for Distance Learning |ref={{harvid|Tarrant County College, 2007}} |access-date=11 April 2007 }}\n* {{Citation |last=Tilakaratne |first=A. |year=2003 |title=The Role of the Sangha in the Conflict in Sri Lanka |journal=Journal of Buddhist Ethics |volume=10 |url=http://blogs.dickinson.edu/buddhistethics/files/2010/12/Tilakaratne.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190805023557/http: