eased on 11 September 2015 by [[Universal Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Visit (2015)|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=blumhouse2015.htm|publisher=boxofficemojo.com|accessdate=10 September 2015}}</ref> In 2017, DeJonge starred as Alice Burbage in the [[TNT (U.S. TV network)|TNT]] series, ''[[Will (TV series)|Will]]''.\n\nIn October 2019, it was announced that DeJonge will star alongside  as [[Priscilla Presley]] in [[Baz Luhrmann]]\u2019s upcoming [[Elvis Presley]] biopic.<ref>{{cite news|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=Baz Luhrmann's Elvis Biopic Casts 'The Society's' Olivia DeJonge as Priscilla Presley|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/baz-luhrmann-elvis-movie-priscilla-presley-olivia-dejonge-1203383589/ |accessdate=4 November 2019|work=variety.com|date=25 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''Good Pretender''\n| Ally\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Polarised''\n| Beth\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Eleven Thirty''\n| Sally\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[The Sisterhood of Night]]''\n| Lavinia Hall\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[The Visit (2015 American film)|The Visit]]''\n| Becca\n| Nominee - [[42nd Saturn Awards]] [[Saturn Award for Best Performance by a Younger Actor|Best Performance by a Younger Actor]]\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Scare Campaign]]''\n| Abby\n| \n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Better Watch Out (film)|Better Watch Out]]''\n| Ashley\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''Undertow''\n|Angie\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''Love and Other Places''\n|Shaz\n|Short film\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Stray Dolls]]''\n| Dallas\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Josie & Jack]]''\n| Josie\n|\n|-\n| 2021\n| ''[[Elvis (2021 film)|Elvis]]''\n| [[Priscilla Presley]]\n| Filming\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Hiding (TV series)|Hiding]]''\n| Shaneen Quigg / Tara Swift\n| 8 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Will (TV series)|Will]]\n| Alice Burbag