{"title_page": "Amara, Romania", "text_new": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = town\n|county                 = Ialomi\u021ba\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Ialomi\u021ba County\n|official_name=Amara\n|image_map=Amara in the Ialomi\u021ba County.svg\n|image_skyline=Centru Administrativ Amara - panoramio.jpg\n|image_shield=ROU IL Amara CoA.jpg\n|leader_name=Ion M\u0103i\u021b\u0103<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.independentonline.ro/2017/06/11/Tandarei-si-Amara-PSD--Fierbinti-PNL-14988?news_page=230 |title=\u021a\u0103nd\u0103rei \u0219i Amara-PSD, Fierbin\u021bi-PNL|newspaper=Independent|lang=ro |date=2017-06-11 |accessdate=2020-04-03 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|leader_party=PSD\n|area_total_km2=70.34\n|coordinates    = {{coord|44|37|12|N|27|19|12|E|region:RO|display=inline,title}}\n|website=http://primaria-amara.ro/\n}}\n\n'''Amara''' is a town in [[Ialomi\u021ba County]], [[Romania]]. It is located in [[B\u0103r\u0103gan Plain|B\u0103r\u0103gan]] on the shores of [[Lake Amara]], at 7&nbsp;km kilometers north of the county capital, [[Slobozia]]. Amara was elevated to town status in 2004.\n\n{{Historical populations\n|source = Census data\n|2002 |7627\n|2011 |7345\n}}\n\n==Demographics==\nAt the census from 2011, Amara, Romania have a total of 7080 residents, 3507 [[male]]s, and 3573 [[female]]s.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{commons category|Amara, Romania}}\n\n{{Ialomi\u0163a County}}\n{{Spa towns in Romania}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Romania|Amara]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Ialomi\u021ba County|Amara]]\n[[Category:Spa towns in Romania]]\n\n\n{{Ialomi\u0163a-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = town\n|county                 = Ialomi\u021ba\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Ialomi\u021ba County\n|official_name=Amara\n|image_map=Amara in the Ialomi\u021ba County.svg\n|image_skyline=Amara01.JPG\n|image_shield=ROU IL Amara CoA.jpg\n|leader_name=Ion M\u0103i\u021b\u0103<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.independentonline.ro/2017/06/11/Tandarei-si-Amara-PSD--Fierbinti-PNL-14988?news_page=230 |title=\u021a\u0103nd\u0103rei \u0219i Amara-PSD, Fierbin\u021bi-PNL|newspaper=Independent|lang=ro |date=2017-06-11 |accessdate=2020-04-03 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|leader_party=PSD\n|area_total_km2=70.34\n|coordinates    = {{coord|44|37|12|N|27|19|12|E|region:RO|display=inline,title}}\n|website=http://primaria-amara.ro/\n}}\n\n'''Amara''' is a town in [[Ialomi\u021ba County]], [[Romania]]. It is located in [[B\u0103r\u0103gan Plain|B\u0103r\u0103gan]] on the shores of [[Lake Amara]], at 7&nbsp;km kilometers north of the county capital, [[Slobozia]]. Amara was elevated to town status in 2004.\n\n{{Historical populations\n|source = Census data\n|2002 |7627\n|2011 |7345\n}}\n\n==Demographics==\nAt the census from 2011, Amara, Romania have a total of 7080 residents, 3507 [[male]]s and 3573 [[female]]s.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{commons category|Amara, Romania}}\n\n{{Ialomi\u0163a County}}\n{{Spa towns in Romania}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Romania|Amara]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Ialomi\u021ba County|Amara]]\n[[Category:Spa towns in Romania]]\n\n\n{{Ialomi\u0163a-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rosenborg BK Fan", "label": "safe", "comment": "Minor edit", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amara,_Romania"}
